//
// T031 — R4 bit-slice and concat spacing per formatting-rules.contract.md §4.
//
// Frozen invariants:
//   * bit slice: `a[7:0]` — no spaces inside `[`, `]`, around `:`
//   * concat:    `{a, b, c}` — one space after each `,`, no spaces
//                 inside `{`, `}` (unless `spaces_inside_braces=true`)
//
// T050 (R4) made this GREEN: `lib/Fmt/LayoutPlanner.cpp` adds
// canonical-layout overrides for `SliceExpr` (`<sub>[<hi>:<lo>]`,
// no spaces inside the brackets or around the colon) and
// `ConcatExpr` (`{<p>, <p>, ...}`, one space after each comma, no
// spaces inside the braces unless `spaces_inside_braces=true`).
//
// `reg` (not `wire`) is used for the initialized declarations
// because S2 forbids `wire <name> = <init>` (use `reg` instead);
// the formatter's strict refusal pipeline rejects the parse before
// any layout work can run.
// RUN: echo 'module m { reg d[8] = a[ 7 : 0 ]; reg e[24] = {a , b , c}; }' | nsl-fmt --stdin | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: a[7:0]
// CHECK-SAME: {a, b, c}
